<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> Quotation: "<i>If revolutionary rational thoughts were expressed in the Age of Reason [the 18th century], they were only made possible because of the long medieval tradition that established the use of reason as one of the most important of human activities</i>". (p. 9) In: Edward Grant: God and Reason in the Middle Ages, Cambridge 2001.</li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/David_C._Lindberg" title="David C. Lindberg">David C. Lindberg</a>, <i>Roger Bacon and the Origins of</i> Perspectiva <i>in the Middle Ages: A Critical Edition and English Translation of Bacon's</i> Perspectiva <i>with Introduction and Notes,</i> Oxford: Oxford University Press, 1996, p. lv <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0198239920" class="internal">ISBN 0-19-823992-0</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> Jeremiah Hackett, "Roger Bacon on <i>Scientia Experimentalis</i>," in Hackett, <i>Roger Bacon and the Sciences,</i> pp. 279–84</li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> Lindberg, "Science as Handmaiden," p. 520</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> Steven J. Williams, "Roger Bacon and His Edition of the Pseudo-Aristotelian <i>Secretum secretorum</i>," <i>Speculum</i>, 69 (1994): 57–73, see p. 71, n. 74.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Lindberg1995-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Lindberg1995_16-0" title="">^</a></b> (p. 70) <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFLindberg.2C_D.C.1995">Lindberg, D.C. (1995). "<a href="http://links.jstor.org/sici?sici=0369-7827(1995)2%3A10%3C60%3AMSAIRC%3E2.0.CO%3B2-H" class="external text" title="http://links.jstor.org/sici?sici=0369-7827(1995)2%3A10%3C60%3AMSAIRC%3E2.0.CO%3B2-H" rel="nofollow">Medieval Science and Its Religious Context</a>". <i>Osiris</i> <b>10</b> (10): 60–79. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1086%2F368743" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1086%2F368743" rel="nofollow">10.1086/368743</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://links.jstor.org/sici?sici=0369-7827(1995)2%3A10%3C60%3AMSAIRC%3E2.0.CO%3B2-H" class="external free" title="http://links.jstor.org/sici?sici=0369-7827(1995)2%3A10%3C60%3AMSAIRC%3E2.0.CO%3B2-H" rel="nofollow">http://links.jstor.org/sici?sici=0369-7827(1995)2%3A10%3C60%3AMSAIRC%3E2.0.CO%3B2-H</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-07-07</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Medieval+Science+and+Its+Religious+Context&amp;rft.jtitle=Osiris&amp;rft.aulast=Lindberg%2C+D.C.&amp;rft.au=Lindberg%2C+D.C.&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.volume=10&amp;rft.issue=10&amp;rft.pages=60%E2%80%9379&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1086%2F368743&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Flinks.jstor.org%2Fsici%3Fsici%3D0369-7827%281995%292%253A10%253C60%253AMSAIRC%253E2.0.CO%253B2-H&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Roger_Bacon"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
